GateScope

Derived-from notice:

- This repository is an independent derivative project based on `AgentScan`
  from `https://github.com/AutoScan/agentscan`.
- The upstream project is distributed under the MIT License.
- This repository does not claim to be the upstream official release.

Key fork-specific work included here:

- Unified runtime control via `agentscanctl`
- Login autofill and one-click login
- Task event persistence and replay
- UI asset-to-vulnerability attribution
- Excel export improvements with asset context
- Full evidence retention for new scans
- YAML-based OpenClaw rule maintenance under `configs/rules/`
- Rule metadata exposure and PoC/CVE normalization
- PoC-priority deduplication over version-only hits

Branding note:

- The public-facing project name used in this repository is `GateScope`.
- Internal Go module paths may still reference the upstream import path for compatibility and to avoid unnecessary refactors.
